	<key>readme</key>
	<string>## Usage

Configure an AWS profile using credentials found in the clipboard via the `sts` keyword.

![Screenshot 1](images/screenshot-1.png)
![Screenshot 2](images/screenshot-2.png)
---
Credentials may be obtained from the AWS access portal or CLI.

From the **AWS access portal**, choose *Option 1* or *Option 2*.
![Access portal option 1](images/access-portal-1.png)
---
![Access portal option 2](images/access-portal-2.png)
Using the **AWS CLI**, run ***aws sts get-session-token*** and copy the output to the clipboard.  You can use any output format supported by the CLI: json, text, table, yaml, or yaml-stream.

## Setup

Install the AWS CLI.</string>
